reviews.text: Had an absolutely flawless lunch here. The food was delicious and innovative, and the service was polished, professional and enthusiastic. It has one Michelin star but would not be surprised to see that increased to two. Would absolutely go back.

A superb meal prepared with real finesse using a lot of Japanese ingredients infused into French cuisine. We went for the longer tasting menu and were extremely happy with the results. From your bread basket through to desserts they really hit every course perfectly.

This is an expensive restaurant, however if there is a business lunch or a special occasion to be celebrated I cannot recommend this place highly enough. Staff are very attentive and the whole meal was excellent.

Creative blend of premium and exclusive Japanese and French ingredients and done superbly by Chef Eric Raty. Wine sommeliers were friendly and helpful. The overall atmosphere was cozy and sophisticated while the service was attentive and pleasant.  

I was actually at the same restaurant having lunch the day before and the menu was totally different and just as great. 

A place I will definitely come back when I need a treat.

Luxury dining done right! The food was impeccable the service was absolutely on point and the decor is delightful. Could not fault our meal in any way. I had the taster menu and every item was genuinely exquisite and we all left agreeing that we were perfectly satisfied. Top, top stuff.

Nice spot for a holiday meal. Good views, good food and good service. 
The Autumn Truffle (mushroom pasta dish) was very good. So was the soy milk dessert.

reviews.text: With excellent art throughout the year , the galleries here are always chopping and changing something new every few months. A real eclectic mix of artists; some well known, others less so, there's also piqnic on the roof for a well earned bevy.

The art was great but the accessibility of the building is horrible. I injured my knee and ankle earlier in the day and despite having a visible limp, the guards had to be asked repeatedly for the lift and only begrudgingly called for the elevator when I was going 3 and 5 floors down. For single floors I just hobbled down because they made such a big production out of it when I was going multiple floors.
Nice building. The janitors downstairs, they are a little pushy because of the crowd they get.
Very very great place to visit. And of cuz to see art and buy art.
House the majority of the quality art galleries  of Hong Kong
